@node MUI "WebVision À About MUI"
                          This application uses


                        MUI - MagicUserInterface

                (c) Copyright 1993-98 by Stefan Stuntz


MUI is a system to generate and maintain graphical user interfaces. With
the  aid  of  a  preferences program, the user of an application has the
ability to customize the outfit according to his personal taste.

MUI is distributed as shareware. To obtain a complete package containing
lots of examples and more information about registration please look for
a  file  called  "muiXXusr.lha"  (XX means the latest version number) on
your local bulletin boards or on public domain disks.

          If you want to register directly, feel free to send


                         DM 30.-  or  US$ 20.-

                                  to

                             Stefan Stuntz
                        Eduard-Spranger-Stra▀e 7
                             80935 M³nchen
                                GERMANY



             Support and online registration is available at

                          http://www.sasg.com/
@endnode

@node History "WebVision À History"
@{u}Version history@{uu}
WebTV 1.0 (13.2.98)
 ÀáFirst release to AmiNet.

WebTV 1.1 (5.3.98)
 ÀáStreaming/server-push video support.
 À HTTP and HTTP Proxy Authorization.
 À Bugfixes (Save as... and autosaving files).
 À Easier camsite configuration, uses a listtree and changes are reflected
   immediatedly in open cams.  No need to close and reopen windows.
 À Easier global configuration from a new settings window.  No more messing
   around with tooltypes/arguments.
 À More webcam sites.
 À First Virtual, US and UK registration available!
 À Better reporting of errors.
 À Requires AmiTCP v3+ instead of V4+ now.
 À And much more...

WebVision 2.0 (15.12.98)
 À Program renamed to avoid clashing with the copyrighted brandname.

 À Norwegian registration address changed, and First Virtual registration
   replaced by RegNet.

 À Many minor bugfixes and optimizations.

 À Major feature: automatic site list update over the Internet from a
   central server. This works two ways, you can both get and submit new
   sites. (registered users only)

 À Added automatic program update, the program can check for and download new
   versions itself.

 À Redesigned Site Edit window, the update delay can now be set freely, the
   slider is gone.  The window is divided into three pagegroups, with the
   advanced options hidden from the sight of new users.

 À New and changed camsite attributes: Image URL, Homepage URL, HTTP
   Referer, Adult content, Don't display pictures, and HTTP User headers.

 À Image autosave revised completely, much more flexible now.

 À Added popup menu to the list of camsites.

 À Added optional and configurable socket timeout.

 À Added support for CyberGraphX video overlays.  Should also work for
   PicassoIV users running Picasso96.  This allows you to view the images
   in 16 bits of color on an 8 bit screen.

 À Added support for my openurl.library.  You can now click an URL in the
   about window, and send webcam URLs to your favourite browser.

 À Menus redesigned and made available from all windows.  Added checkmarks to
   quickly toggle the most common options.

 À Most commandline arguments and all tooltypes are gone.  Configuration
   should be done from within the program, there are too many options for
   commandline usage now.

 À And much more...

WebVision 2.1 (17.2.99)
 À Added scaling of images, including submenu with presets in the Site menu.

 ÀáAdded busypointer while saving/loading sites.

 À Added option to disable online check, for example to trigger dial-on-demand.
   (John S Burger)

 À Simplified MiamiIsOnline() check and some MUI code for smaller size.

 À Changed HTTP request code to allow non-HTTP requests when using a proxy.

 À Changed HTTP response parser to allow for a bit of non-RFC compliance on
   the server part. (Buggy site supplied by Skyclad)

 À Opening and closing the aboutwindow had a high probability of leaving an
   orphan "WebVision Flame Render Process" in the system.  Should be
   completely harmless, but a waste of resources of course.

 À Added workaround to Listtree.mcc bug that would seem to delete sites and
   groups outside the "Automatically updated" group, though it was only a
   visual effect. (David Gerber)

 À Fixed a couple of cases where "Pragma" and "Proxy-Authorization" headers
   would be sent even if they shouldn't.

 À Camlist update on startup wouldn't work unless program update check was
   enabled too.

WebVision 2.2 (26.9.99)
 À The &e expansion character only worked right when placed at the end of a
   filename. (Dean Husby)

 À Sigh...  the WV 2.1 Listtree.mcc workaround wasn't right, I think I
   finally identified the real problem and worked around it.  An annoying
   sideeffect of this "fix" is that closed groups will be opened if any sites
   need to be deleted inside them.
   (Sigbj°rn Skjµret)

 À Changed back to prefer Textinput.mcc over BetterString.mcc.

 À Changed the way the CGX VideoLayer is attached to the window, this should
   cure the problem with overwriting the windowborder. (Frank Mariak)

 À Now uses Popplaceholder.mcc by Marcin Or¯owski for autosave formatting codes.
   (PiKe)

 À Cloning enhanced, you can now clone groups, and the cloned node is scrolled 
   into view.
   (PiKe)

 ÀáAdded a contextmenu over the camwindows, with same entries as the Site menu.

@endnode

